d:["$","article",null,{"className":"bg-white","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-6","children":["$","nav",null,{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600","children":[["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-blue-600","children":"Home"}],[["$","div","/high-chairs",{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-400","children":"/"}],["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/high-chairs","className":"hover:text-blue-600","children":"High Chairs"}]]}],["$","div","/high-chairs/portable-high-chairs-for-travel",{"className":"flex items-center space-x-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-400","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-gray-900 font-medium","children":"Portable High Chairs for Travel and Restaurants: Options That Go With You"}]]}]]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 border-b border-gray-200","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Portable High Chairs for Travel and Restaurants: Options That Go With You"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-gray-600","children":"Find the best portable high chairs for travel, restaurants, and on-the-go feeding. Compare clip-on chairs, booster seats, and travel-friendly options with pros and cons."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-sm max-w-none","children":[["$","h2","0",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Introduction"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"A high chair becomes a necessity the moment your baby starts eating solid foods, but traditional full-size chairs don't travel. Whether you're visiting relatives, dining at restaurants, or staying in a vacation rental, you need a feeding solution that's portable. Portable high chairs range from minimalist clip-on chairs (nearly weightless) to full-size foldables (transportable but still substantial). This guide compares options, explains the trade-offs, and helps you choose the right portable solution for your lifestyle."}],["$","h2","2",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"The Portable High Chair Challenge"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Traditional full-size high chairs are heavy (24-35 lbs), bulky, and tied to a single location. Portable options sacrifice comfort and features for lightness and compactness. The spectrum runs from ultra-minimal (clip-on chair, 2 lbs) to moderately portable (foldable convertible, 25 lbs). Most families find the solution in the middle—a lightweight travel seat that's usable but more minimal than home chairs."}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Clip-On and Hook-On Chairs"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"The most minimal portable option: a seat that clips or attaches to an existing table edge."}],["$","h2","6",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# How They Work"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"A clip or hook mechanism grips the table edge. The seat suspends your baby at table height. No separate base or legs—just attachment to the table. Examples: Inglesina Fast Table, Summer Infant Pop Seat, Babybjörn Table Chair."}],["$","h2","8",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Advantages"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Weightless**: 2-3 lbs. Fits in a diaper bag or small backpack. You'll forget you're carrying it."}],"$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d","$L2e","$L2f","$L30","$L31","$L32","$L33","$L34","$L35","$L36","$L37","$L38","$L39","$L3a","$L3b","$L3c","$L3d","$L3e","$L3f","$L40","$L41","$L42","$L43","$L44","$L45","$L46","$L47","$L48","$L49","$L4a","$L4b","$L4c","$L4d","$L4e","$L4f","$L50","$L51","$L52","$L53","$L54","$L55","$L56","$L57","$L58","$L59","$L5a","$L5b","$L5c","$L5d","$L5e","$L5f","$L60","$L61","$L62","$L63","$L64","$L65","$L66","$L67","$L68","$L69","$L6a","$L6b","$L6c","$L6d","$L6e","$L6f","$L70","$L71","$L72","$L73","$L74","$L75","$L76","$L77","$L78","$L79","$L7a","$L7b","$L7c","$L7d","$L7e"]}]}],"$L7f","$L80","$L81"]}]
82:I[31175,["/_next/static/chunks/7bb08ad39a4b23f0.js","/_next/static/chunks/5935fefdd9fc8f83.js"],"default"]
15:["$","p","10",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**No Floor Space**: Doesn't occupy dining table real estate. In small hotel rooms or crowded restaurants, this is transformative. You're not pushing furniture around."}]
16:["$","p","11",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Simple Setup**: Clip to table, place baby, feed. No tools, no assembly. Takes 30 seconds."}]
17:["$","p","12",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Affordable**: $60-$200 range. Budget-friendly compared to convertible chairs."}]
18:["$","p","13",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Portable**: Can be stored in suitcases, backpacks, or car seats. Travels anywhere."}]
19:["$","h2","14",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Disadvantages"}]
1a:["$","p","15",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Weight Limits**: Typically 80-90 lbs max, but practically unsuitable for children heavier than 50-60 lbs (ages 2-3+)."}]
1b:["$","p","16",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Table Dependency**: Requires a table (rigid, stable, correct height). Doesn't work without one. In cars, parks, or beach settings—not feasible."}]
1c:["$","p","17",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Limited Comfort**: Minimal padding. No recline. No toys or entertainment. Functional, not cozy."}]
1d:["$","p","18",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Stability Concerns**: On flimsy tables or uneven surfaces, the chair wobbles. Not suitable for boisterous toddlers who shift weight or stand."}]
1e:["$","p","19",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Limited Duration**: Best for short meals (under 30 minutes). Extended feeding is uncomfortable."}]
1f:["$","p","20",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Doesn't Work at Home**: For daily at-home feeding, a clip-on chair is tedious. You need a permanent solution."}]
20:["$","h2","21",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Best For"}]
21:["$","ul","22",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Restaurants (clip to dining table, feed quickly, remove)"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Visiting relatives (your parent's kitchen table)"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Travel to hotels with dining areas"}],["$","li","3",{"children":"Short trips where your child eats briefly then leaves the chair"}]]}]
22:["$","h2","23",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Less Suitable For"}]
23:["$","ul","24",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Primary feeding solution (use a real high chair at home)"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Toddlers 2+ years (too heavy or unstable for older children)"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Extended meals (no comfort features)"}],["$","li","3",{"children":"Outdoor settings (no table nearby)"}]]}]
24:["$","h2","25",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Portable Booster Seats"}]
25:["$","p","26",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"A lightweight fabric seat that sits on a regular chair and raises your baby to table height."}]
26:["$","h2","27",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# How They Work"}]
27:["$","p","28",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"The booster is a fabric-and-frame structure that straps to a regular dining chair. Your baby sits in the booster, which lifts them to table height. Examples: Baby Delight Go With Me, Summer Infant Pop Seat Portable, Kabooki Seat."}]
28:["$","h2","29",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Advantages"}]
29:["$","p","30",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Ultra-Portable**: Weighs under 2 lbs (often under 1 lb). Folds to smaller than a pillow. Fits in luggage or backpack."}]
2a:["$","p","31",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Works Without a Table**: Unlike clip-on chairs, boosters work with any chair—dining chair, park bench, someone's lap (if tethered). More flexible setup."}]
2b:["$","p","32",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Affordable**: $40-$120 range. Budget-friendly."}]
2c:["$","p","33",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Age Range**: Suitable from 8 months to 2-3 years (light enough that portability matters)."}]
2d:["$","h2","34",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Disadvantages"}]
2e:["$","p","35",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Minimal Padding**: Sits directly on the chair. No comfort features. Not cozy for long feeding sessions."}]
2f:["$","p","36",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Instability on Soft Chairs**: If placed on a soft couch or fabric chair, the booster wobbles and sinks. Needs a firm, upright chair."}]
30:["$","p","37",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**No Tray Option**: Most portable boosters don't have attached trays. Your baby can reach the parent's plate (distracting, messy)."}]
31:["$","p","38",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Difficult Transitions**: Moving your baby in and out of a booster on someone else's furniture is awkward."}]
32:["$","p","39",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Not for Infants**: Designed for babies 8 months+. Too large and unstable for younger infants."}]
33:["$","h2","40",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Best For"}]
34:["$","ul","41",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Travel where you'll use existing chairs (hotels, relatives' homes, restaurants)"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Short feeding occasions (15-30 minutes)"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Families who travel frequently and value portability over comfort"}],["$","li","3",{"children":"Babies 8 months to 2 years"}]]}]
35:["$","h2","42",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Less Suitable For"}]
36:["$","ul","43",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Primary home feeding (get a real high chair instead)"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Boisterous toddlers who move a lot"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Long meals or extended sitting"}],["$","li","3",{"children":"Newborns and young infants (6 months and younger)"}]]}]
37:["$","h2","44",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Foldable Full-Size High Chairs"}]
38:["$","p","45",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Some full-size chairs fold for transport without sacrificing functionality."}]
39:["$","h2","46",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# How They Work"}]
3a:["$","p","47",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"A full-size high chair (full seat, tray, harness) that folds to a compact size for storage or transport. Examples: IKEA Antilop, Chicco Polly, Joovy Nook."}]
3b:["$","h2","48",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Advantages"}]
3c:["$","p","49",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Full Functionality**: While at the destination, it functions as a normal high chair—comfortable, full tray, harness, proper support."}]
3d:["$","p","50",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reusable for Multiple Children**: A foldable chair serves multiple kids over years. Good long-term value."}]
3e:["$","p","51",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Stability**: Unlike clip-on or booster options, a full-size chair is rock-solid. No wobbling or tipping concerns."}]
3f:["$","p","52",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Comfortable**: Padded seat, spacious design, features (recline, toys, etc.)."}]
40:["$","p","53",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Doesn't Require a Table**: Functions independently, so it works anywhere."}]
41:["$","h2","54",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Disadvantages"}]
42:["$","p","55",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Still Heavy**: Foldable models are still 18-25 lbs. Lighter than non-folding (24-35 lbs) but heavier than clip-on (2-3 lbs)."}]
43:["$","p","56",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Large When Folded**: Compact-for-a-chair still means a bulky item to pack. Fits in car trunks, but not luggage or carry-on."}]
44:["$","p","57",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Setup Labor**: Folding and unfolding takes time and effort. If you're traveling for a weekend, it's worth it. For a quick restaurant meal, it's overkill."}]
45:["$","p","58",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Not Suited for Minimal Travel**: If you take short trips where you'll dine out mostly, a foldable high chair is unnecessary bulk."}]
46:["$","h2","59",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Best For"}]
47:["$","ul","60",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Extended vacations (1+ weeks) where you'll stay in one place and need daily feeding"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Visiting relatives for extended periods where you'll install at their home"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Families who travel frequently enough to justify keeping a second chair at a vacation home"}],["$","li","3",{"children":"Older babies and toddlers (1+ years)"}]]}]
48:["$","h2","61",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Less Suitable For"}]
49:["$","ul","62",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"Quick weekend getaways where you'll mostly eat at restaurants"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"Air travel (airlines are reluctant to gate-check foldables due to size)"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"Frequent relocations or frequent restaurant dining"}]]}]
4a:["$","h2","63",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Travel-Specific Features to Evaluate"}]
4b:["$","h2","64",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Tray Design"}]
4c:["$","p","65",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Attached vs. Removable**: Some boosters and clip-on chairs don't have trays. Removable trays are nice; attached trays are simpler. In travel scenarios, removable trays are easier to clean (use a hotel sink)."}]
4d:["$","p","66",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Dishwasher-Safe**: Critical for travel. Hand-scrubbing trays in hotel sinks is tedious. Dishwasher-safe trays are a huge convenience."}]
4e:["$","h2","67",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Cleaning Ease"}]
4f:["$","p","68",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Wipeable Seat**: Fabric seats collect food and spills. A plastic or wipeable seat dries faster and doesn't harbor bacteria."}]
50:["$","p","69",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Removable Covers**: If the seat cover is removable and washable, cleaning is easier. Some chairs don't allow removal."}]
51:["$","h2","70",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Weight Limits"}]
52:["$","p","71",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Check the weight limit for your baby's age and size. A clip-on suitable for 6-month-olds might be unsuitable for 18-month-olds."}]
53:["$","h2","72",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Foldability and Storage"}]
54:["$","p","73",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"How small does it fold? Does it fit your luggage? Does it fit in a car trunk? Is the folding mechanism easy or require tools?"}]
55:["$","h2","74",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Real-World Scenarios: What to Buy"}]
56:["$","h2","75",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Scenario 1: Frequent Restaurant Dining"}]
57:["$","p","76",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Your situation**: You eat out 2-3 times per week. Your baby is 6-18 months old."}]
58:["$","p","77",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Best option**: Clip-on chair (Inglesina Fast Table, $150-$200)"}]
59:["$","p","78",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reasoning**: Ultra-portable, quick setup, suitable for short meals. No luggage burden. Cost is low enough to justify a single-use travel purchase."}]
5a:["$","p","79",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Setup**: Keep in your car or diaper bag. Bring to restaurants. Clip to table, feed, and clip off."}]
5b:["$","h2","80",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Scenario 2: One-Week Vacation"}]
5c:["$","p","81",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Your situation**: You're staying in a vacation rental for a week. Your baby eats 3 meals daily."}]
5d:["$","p","82",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Best option**: Lightweight foldable chair (IKEA Antilop, $80-$150) or portable booster (Baby Delight Go With Me, $60-$120)"}]
5e:["$","p","83",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reasoning**: You need a full-featured feeding solution for daily use. Lightweight foldables are transportable (fit in car trunk) but still functional. If the vacation rental has a sturdy dining table, a booster is sufficient."}]
5f:["$","p","84",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Setup**: Pack the chair in your car. Set up at the vacation home. Use for the week. Fold and return."}]
60:["$","h2","85",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Scenario 3: Frequent Travel to Relatives"}]
61:["$","p","86",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Your situation**: You visit grandparents' house monthly for extended weekends (2-3 days)."}]
62:["$","p","87",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Best option**: Lightweight foldable chair stored at grandparents' home OR a booster seat that travels in your car"}]
63:["$","p","88",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reasoning**: If you're visiting monthly, keeping a dedicated chair at their home is practical (saves packing/unpacking). If you prefer to travel light, a booster seat lives in your car and gets set up at their dining table."}]
64:["$","p","89",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Setup**: Either pre-position a chair at their home (they maintain it) or bring a booster seat that folds into your car."}]
65:["$","h2","90",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Scenario 4: Quick Day Trips"}]
66:["$","p","91",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Your situation**: You take day trips to parks, stores, or nearby relatives. Your child eats snacks and maybe lunch away from home."}]
67:["$","p","92",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Best option**: Skip the portable high chair. Use a restaurant high chair (provide by the venue) or hold your baby while they eat."}]
68:["$","p","93",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reasoning**: For short absences (under 3 hours), a portable high chair is overkill. Your baby can eat in your lap or in a restaurant-provided chair."}]
69:["$","h2","94",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"# Scenario 5: Traveling by Air"}]
6a:["$","p","95",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Your situation**: You're flying to visit relatives or on vacation. Your baby is 6-24 months."}]
6b:["$","p","96",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Best option**: Clip-on chair (Inglesina Fast Table) or booster seat (Baby Delight Go With Me)"}]
6c:["$","p","97",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Reasoning**: Foldable full-size chairs are difficult to fly with (they're too large for luggage and airlines are reluctant to gate-check them due to size). Ultra-portable options (clip-on, booster) fit in carry-on or checked luggage."}]
6d:["$","p","98",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Setup**: Pack the portable chair in your luggage. At your destination, use it at the dining table or with rental furniture."}]
6e:["$","h2","99",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Hybrid Approach: Multiple Portable Options"}]
6f:["$","p","100",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Many families use a combination:"}]
70:["$","ul","101",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":"**At home**: Full-size convertible high chair ($250-$400)"}],["$","li","1",{"children":"**Restaurants and quick trips**: Clip-on chair ($150) or booster ($80)"}],["$","li","2",{"children":"**Extended vacations**: Foldable portable chair ($150) or keep a second full-size at relatives' home"}]]}]
71:["$","p","102",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"This approach eliminates compromise—each situation has the right tool."}]
72:["$","p","103",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Cost**: ~$400-600 total for three options"}]
73:["$","p","104",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Benefit**: Optimal for every situation without forcing trade-offs"}]
74:["$","h2","105",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"When to Transition Out of Portable Options"}]
75:["$","p","106",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Around age 2-3 years, children are often too large or too boisterous for portable chairs. They graduate to:\n- Regular dining chairs with a cushion\n- Booster seats on regular chairs (different from portable boosters—these are permanent and more stable)\n- Sitting at the table without any special seat"}]
76:["$","p","107",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"At this stage, portable high chairs become unnecessary."}]
77:["$","h2","108",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Cleaning and Maintenance for Travel Chairs"}]
78:["$","p","109",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Clip-On Chairs**: Wipe after each meal. Wash tray with dish soap and dry. Fabric portions air-dry quickly."}]
79:["$","p","110",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Booster Seats**: Wipe the bottom (stays clean), wash the tray if present. Most have removable, washable fabric covers—rinse in a sink."}]
7a:["$","p","111",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"**Foldable Chairs**: Wipe immediately after meals (food dries on and becomes hard to clean). Many offer dishwasher-safe trays and removable, washable covers."}]
7b:["$","h2","112",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
7c:["$","p","113",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Portable high chairs are essential if you feed your baby away from home frequently. The best option depends on how often you travel, how long you stay, and whether your destinations have dining tables or chairs available."}]
7d:["$","p","114",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Clip-on chairs are ideal for restaurants and quick trips. Booster seats work for flexible seating (tables, chairs, benches). Foldable full-size chairs are best for extended stays where you need full functionality daily."}]
7e:["$","p","115",{"className":"text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Most families find that a combination (a home high chair plus a lightweight portable option) eliminates compromise. Choose the portable option that matches your most common travel scenario, and don't over-invest in portability if you rarely eat away from home."}]
7f:["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6","children":"More High Chair Resources"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4","children":[["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/high-chairs","className":"p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2","children":"Back to Comparison"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-600","children":"View all 13 high chairs with interactive filters and ratings."}]]}],["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/high-chairs/best-high-chairs-for-small-spaces","className":"p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2","children":"Small Spaces Guide"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-600","children":"Find compact and foldable options for apartments and tiny homes."}]]}],["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/high-chairs/wooden-vs-plastic-high-chairs","className":"p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2","children":"Materials Comparison"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-600","children":"Compare wood and plastic for durability, cleaning, and aesthetics."}]]}],["$","$L5",null,{"href":"/high-chairs/high-chair-safety-checklist","className":"p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:shadow-md transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2","children":"Safety Guide"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-600","children":"Learn harness types, stability testing, and recall information."}]]}]]}]]}]
